definitions.definition: A short sequence of bits (binary digits) that can be operated on as a unit by a computer ; the smallest usable machine word .
A unit of computing storage equal to eight bits , which can represent any of 256 distinct values.
examples: The word “hello” fits into five bytes of ASCII code.
